snippet.description:
Ariana Grande - positions (Official Live Performance) | Vevo

If our Official Live Performances of â€œpovâ€ and â€œsafety netâ€ reveal anything, itâ€™s that Ariana Grande excels at her job because sheâ€™s so passionate about the results. You donâ€™t hit the high notes, you donâ€™t exude candor, and you donâ€™t make pop music as moving as she does without crossing the Tâ€™s and dotting the Iâ€™s. A very cool Cali session with the look and feel of a cozy little meadow was a perfect place to turn some of the best tunes on â€˜Positionsâ€™ into utterly memorable performances. Go Team Ari. In a typically inventive move, our hero chose to loop her vocals when it came time to perform the albumâ€™s title track. Watch her augment the bandâ€™s moves with a little layering of her voice. As she references both the kitchen and the bedroom in her lyrics, the sound stacks up, taking on its own internal rhythm. Beautiful.

snippet.description:
ITâ€™S TIME. #DuneMovie coming October 22.

-----------------

Oscar nominee Denis Villeneuve (â€œArrival,â€ â€œBlade Runner 2049â€) directs Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Picturesâ€™ â€œDune,â€ the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbertâ€™s seminal bestseller of the same name.

A mythic and emotionally charged heroâ€™s journey, â€œDuneâ€ tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet in the universe to ensure the future of his family and his people. As malevolent forces explode into conflict over the planetâ€™s exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existenceâ€”a commodity capable of unlocking humanityâ€™s greatest potentialâ€”only those who can conquer their fear will survive.

The film stars Oscar nominee TimothÃ©e Chalamet (â€œCall Me by Your Name,â€ â€œLittle Womenâ€), Rebecca Ferguson (â€œStephen Kingâ€™s Doctor Sleep,â€ â€œMission: Impossible â€“ Falloutâ€), Oscar Isaac (the â€œStar Warsâ€ franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (â€œMilk,â€ â€œAvengers: Infinity Warâ€), Stellan SkarsgÃ¥rd (HBOâ€™s â€œChernobyl,â€ â€œAvengers: Age of Ultronâ€), Dave Bautista (the â€œGuardians of the Galaxyâ€ films, â€œAvengers: Endgameâ€), Stephen McKinley Henderson (â€œFences,â€ â€œLady Birdâ€), Zendaya (â€œSpider-Man: Homecoming,â€ HBOâ€™s â€œEuphoriaâ€), Chang Chen (â€œMr. Long,â€ â€œCrouching Tiger, Hidden Dragonâ€), David Dastmalchian (â€œBlade Runner 2049,â€ â€œThe Dark Knightâ€), Sharon Duncan-Brewster (â€œRogue One: A Star Wars Story,â€ Netflixâ€™s â€œSex Educationâ€), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (â€œ45 Years,â€ â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€), with Jason Momoa (â€œAquaman,â€ HBOâ€™s â€œGame of Thronesâ€), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (â€œNo Country for Old Men,â€ â€œSkyfallâ€).

Villeneuve directed â€œDuneâ€ from a screenplay by Jon Spaihts and Villeneuve and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert. Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter and Joe Caracciolo, Jr. The executive producers are Tanya Lapointe, Joshua Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert.

Behind the scenes, Villeneuve reteamed with two-time Oscar-nominated production designer Patrice Vermette (â€œArrival,â€ â€œSicario,â€ â€œThe Young Victoriaâ€), two-time Oscar-nominated editor Joe Walker (â€œBlade Runner 2049,â€ â€œArrival,â€ â€œ12 Years a Slaveâ€), two-time Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert (â€œFirst Man,â€ â€œBlade Runner 2049â€), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (â€œBlade Runner 2049â€). He also collaborated for the first time with Oscar-nominated director of photography Greig Fraser (â€œLion,â€ â€œZero Dark Thirty,â€ â€œRogue One: A Star Wars Storyâ€); three-time Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West (â€œThe Revenant,â€ â€œThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,â€ â€œQuillsâ€) and costume designer Robert Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (â€œThe Dark Knightâ€ trilogy, â€œInceptionâ€). Oscar-winning and multiple Oscar-nominated composer Hans Zimmer (â€œBlade Runner 2049,â€ â€œInception,â€ â€œGladiator,â€ â€œThe Lion Kingâ€) is creating the score.

Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures Present a Legendary Pictures Production, a Film by Denis Villeneuve, â€œDune.â€ The film is slated to be released in select theaters in 2D and 3D and IMAX and on HBO Max on October 22, 2021 and will be available on HBO Maxâ€™s Ad-Free plan in 4K UHD, HDR10, Dolby Vision and Dolby Atmos (English Only) on supported devices for 31 days from theatrical release.

The film has been rated PG-13 for sequences of strong violence, some disturbing images and suggestive material.
